    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Add your<strong> butternut squash cubes</strong> to a baking tray with a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray into the oven for 20-25 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tangy-vegetable-pad-thai/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> pepper strips</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tangy-vegetable-pad-thai/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>rice noodles</strong> to a pot and cover with <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Boil over a high heat for 4-5 min or until softened with a slight bite</p><p>Once softened, drain the <strong>noodles</strong>, run them under <strong>cold water</strong>, then return to the pot with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and set aside</p><p>Tip: The oil prevents the noodles from sticking together!</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tangy-vegetable-pad-thai/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel lengths off your <strong>courgette[s] </strong>until you end up with a pile of courgette ribbons</p><p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add your<strong> tamarind paste</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>mirin</strong>, <strong>sriracha </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), the juice of <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lime</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and give it all a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>pad Thai sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tangy-vegetable-pad-thai/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pepper has softened, add the <strong>courgette ribbons </strong>and <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>garlic </strong>to the pan and cook for 1-2 min until fragrant, then remove from the heat</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tangy-vegetable-pad-thai/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, crush your <strong>roasted peanuts</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin</strong></p><p>Tip: If you don't have a rolling pin, just chop them roughly!</p><p>Chop your <strong>Thai basil </strong>and <strong>coriander</strong> roughly, including the stalks</p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>lime</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tangy-vegetable-pad-thai/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium-high heat and add the <strong>drained noodles</strong> along with the<strong> roasted butternut squash</strong> and <strong>pad Thai sauce </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Stir through <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>chopped Thai basil</strong> and <strong>coriander</strong> (save the rest for garnish!) \u2013 this is your <strong>tangy</strong> <strong>vegetable pad Thai</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tangy-vegetable-pad-thai/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>To serve, sprinkle the<strong> remaining chopped Thai basil </strong>and <strong>coriander</strong> and the <strong>crushed peanuts</strong> all over the <strong>tangy vegetable pad Thai</strong></p><p>Garnish with a <strong>lime wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
